<DOC><DOCNO> AP880408-0099 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-08-88 1241EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Nigeria-Corruption     04-08 0087</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Nigeria-Corruption,0089</SECOND><HEAD>Passport Officers Arrested For Corruption</HEAD><DATELINE>ABIDJAN, Ivory Coast (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   All the members of the passportoffice in Minna in east-central Nigeria have been arrested oncharges of selling passports to foreign nationals, Nigerian stateradio reported Friday.   The report, monitored in Abidjan, said the passport officialswere collecting an illegal fee of about $17 to $24 in addition tothe official $24 charge.   Police said the fraud was uncovered when immigration officialsarrested Niger nationals who could not speak any of Nigeria'slanguages.</TEXT></DOC>